{
  "uuid": "d513a4db67e1334554a3e1a72d8a5728",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "RESTAURANT CAPTAIN",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>1. Greets guests and responds to guest inquiries and requests in a prompt and professional manner.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>2. Supervises the service rendered and delivery of ordered items by F&amp;B attendants is timely and consistent with the restaurant’s standards.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>3. Equips with updated knowledge of the restaurant’s products and services</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>4. Resolves customers’ complaints during shift and logs all complaints for further follow-up actions.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>5. Conducts shift briefings to ensure restaurant activities and operational requirements are known to staff on duty.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>6. Checks and maintains stock for F&amp;B supplies e.g. cutleries, dinnerware, glassware, etc. for smooth operations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>7. Manage table reservation system and service crew</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>8. Oversees the maintenance cycle for service equipment.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>9. Adhere to hygiene and safety standards</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>10. Adheres to local regulations concerning health, safety, or other compliance requirements, as well as the company’s standard operating procedures</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>11. Handles other adhoc duties as and when assigned by Assistant Manager / F&amp;B Manager.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>1. Demonstrated ability to manage crew members</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>2. 2 years of relevant experience in a similar capacity</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>3. Demonstrated ability to interact with customers, employees, and third parties</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>4. Possesses strong problem-solving and training abilities</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>5. Interaction with guests in Mandarin &amp; English is essential</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>6. Customer service-oriented mindset</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>7. Able to multi-task in a fast-paced environment</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Working Hours:</strong> 6 days work week, including weekend &amp; PH.</p>",
